doc.after: Canadian Airlines International was the principal subsidiary of its parent company Canadian Airlines Corporation The new airline was formed on March 27 1987 when Pacific Western Airlines purchased Canadian Pacific Air Lines which operated as CP Air for a number of years which in turn had recently acquired Eastern Provincial Airways and Nordair
